        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-679",
        "content": "In other studios I had seen music employed in the making of soberly dramatic scenes, solely as an aid to the actors, enabling them to get into the atmosphere of their work more quickly and naturally.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
